{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"142339-where-did-my-call-go","title":"Where Did My Call Go?","description":"When we make phone calls, our voice is able to travel to places that are far away. Have you ever wondered how cell phones can make a voice travel over long distances?","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"4","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Samidha Gunjal"],"illustrators":["Samidha Gunjal"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Pratham Books","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/142339-where-did-my-call-go"},"cover":{"card":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/216365/size3/d4a5d158d2688512fdccc901a63c125c.jpg","large":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/216365/size6/d4a5d158d2688512fdccc901a63c125c.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192508/size6/5b28ece28ad4c5176ca175b38f0ca44d.gif","text":"When we speak into the phone,\nour voice enters it in the form\nof sound waves.","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192621/size6/b3f0fe59e223b55aca0af7c1e49144b5.gif","text":"The sound waves rush into the microphone and are changed into electrical signals.\nMicrophone","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192509/size6/2badb19f21f833939ffc7751f11dec91.gif","text":"The phone’s antenna changes the electrical signals into electromagnetic waves.\nThese waves are picked up by the closest cell tower...","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192510/size6/4545f229e5425aa7494a54c525505c68.gif","text":"and then sent to a large cell tower.","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192512/size6/e4bc8da3f178379bb00cb80f6fa7aa13.gif","text":"The large cell tower passes on these waves as signals through wires, where they travel...","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192513/size6/e96d9766e533ee6c0a2c0271b5aebadf.gif","text":"along mountains...\nover roads...\nand even undersea...","words":null},{"n":7,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192514/size6/c7e11c16267e3317ee6c7ddf84c010bc.gif","text":"until finally, the signal reaches the large tower closest to the person being called.","words":null},{"n":8,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192515/size6/9ec7bc6fa1cafcb05cc5a7dd22297d8f.gif","text":"9/16","words":null},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192479/size6/2b6a1d9274eb33004140d1f42f47f98d.gif","text":"The large tower then converts the signal into electromagnetic waves...","words":null},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192480/size6/b6d109fcf84ff5be7c45c56bf7460400.gif","text":"and sends it to the cell tower closest to the phone you are calling.","words":null},{"n":11,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192518/size6/461be86e03be62ecdce748cf5c141824.gif","text":"12/16","words":null},{"n":12,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192482/size6/d8db8a9e3f0100635d8f26b02e026cd3.gif","text":"The phone’s antenna receives the electromagnetic waves.\nAnd the phone changes the waves into electrical signals.","words":null},{"n":13,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192622/size6/cf0fbded5aafd7ec32b16ee8e7523861.gif","text":"Finally, the electrical signals are converted back into sound waves using the speaker.\nSpeaker","words":null},{"n":14,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/200043/size6/3a8cf2c607df08fad60add6e8c710c8a.gif","text":"And that’s how sound is heard on the other side.","words":null},{"n":15,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/192520/size6/34195c86f41a3f5c8083594ab8507107.gif","text":"Sound waves\nElectrical signals\nElectromagnetic waves\nSmall cell tower\nLarge cell tower\nUnderground wires\nLarge cell tower\nSmall cell tower\nElectromagnetic\nwaves\nElectrical signals\nSound waves\nHow a Call Travels","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":15,"words":190}}